  exact ring-element area identity (not float), unreduced cone angle exactly 2*pi at every
  vertex, torus complex chi=0 with every edge 2-sided, faces simple + consistently oriented.
- k=2 proven two-sided: k>=2 from cyclic-word inequivalence of the two counted orbits
  (no isometry can merge distinct types — E3/E4 words (d,3,p,3) vs (d,p,3,3) are NOT
  rotation/reversal equivalent, checked exhaustively); k<=2 from an exhibited symmetry group
  achieving 2 orbits (E1: order 12, E2: order 8, E3/E4: order 4 per cell).
- Overlap-freeness: closed by the covering-degree argument (local isometry onto R^2/Lambda,
  exact equal areas force degree 1 => embedding). Residues: the covering lemma is a paper
  argument; face-simplicity signs verified in float (margins 0.26..1.0 vs 1e-12) — both
  upgradeable to exact if the thesis wants zero float.
- E2 caveat: its k=2 needs (12*p4,12*d20) treated as a non-counting fill; Agent 1's primary-
  source read (2004 pp.21-22) covers exactly this case. E3/E4 have no fills: convention-free.

